Lastly, (to passe ouer in silence many other Arguments, yea, and some few Signes shortly to be fulfilled, whereof I distinctly entreate in the ensuing Treatise) the iust Iudge of the world must needs giue perfect rest and glory to his troubled Saints and seruants;
         2. Thess. 1.7.8.
       and of necessity render vengeance vnto his, and their, implacable enemies.
